---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="MIW Architects — case study — JPX Web Development Co."
  description="Studio website and project gallery built for MIW Architects."
>
  <div class="max-w-[760px] mx-auto px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <a href="/#work" class="link-ghost text-[14px] mb-8">
      <span class="arr" style="transform: rotate(180deg);">→</span> Back to work
    </a>

    <span class="tag">published</span>
    <h1 class="text-[36px] md:text-[46px] mt-5 mb-3">MIW Architects</h1>
    <p class="text-[18px] max-w-[46ch] mb-8" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">
      A minimalist marketing site and project gallery for an architecture studio — built to let the work speak
      for itself.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-10">
      <a href="https://miwarchitects.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tag" style="text-decoration: none;">
        miwarchitects.com ↗
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card glass mb-10">
      <div class="browser-chrome">
        <div class="browser-chrome__bar"><i></i><i></i><i></i><span>miwarchitects.com</span></div>
        <div class="card-shot">
          <img
            src="https://api.microlink.io/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmiwarchitects.com&screenshot=true&meta=false&embed=screenshot.url"
            alt="MIW Architects homepage"
            loading="lazy"
            style="object-fit: cover;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-case">
      <h2>The brief</h2>
      <p>
        An architecture studio's site lives or dies on one thing: whether the photography and the buildings get out
        of their own way. MIW's work is the whole pitch — the site's job is to present it cleanly and then step
        aside, not compete with it.
      </p>

      <h2>What I built</h2>
      <p>
        A marketing site and project gallery with a simple, consistent structure — Home, Projects, About, Contact,
        Blog — so the studio can drop in new work as projects wrap without touching layout or code. No heavy
        animation, no template bloat, just fast pages that put the images first.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 flex items-center gap-5">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-neu inline-block">Book a 20-min call</a>
      <a class="link-ghost" href="/#work">More work <span class="arr">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
